reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fun little tow truck but not very durable
reviews.reviewText: I bought this for my 4 year old son. It was smaller and less sturdy than I was expecting it to be. He loved it, but the tow line broke within a week and I had to make a new one myself.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 19, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Tow truck with a car
reviews.reviewText: I got this for my almost 3yo boy. Yes he loves the truck we got it today I can already see where problems will occur and the cab hinge is already ready to break it appears. Also this is a pull back and let go kind of toy. The noises it makes are LOUD very very loud the horn noise will make u want to put pencils in your ears and bust your own ear drums to keep from having to hear that high pitch loud noise. But it’s a cool little truck

reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not what I expected
reviews.reviewText: I ended up returning this toy. I thought that it would be able to pull all cars on its tow, but sadly only the car it came with was able to be pulled.My son has about 100 hot wheels and disney cars, cars that he wanted to use on it and none fit.So we returned this. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 18, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My Grandsons Fight Over One but It's Not Too Expensive to Buy Two!
reviews.reviewText: My daughter has three boys under 4. ALL of them love trucks. One of the boys received this tow truck as a gift but it caused arguments--and yes, my angels would fight over it. When my daughter asked me to buy the same one, I protested. She didn't want another because the first one was out of commission. She wanted it so the two biggest boys (still pretty little) could each have one. I get it. Lots of the little pieces are functional. Lights, sounds, hoist and cars to tow. . . it seems like everything works. The small size is perfect for those (usually) grubby little hands with fingers capable of getting into trouble with many things. So i sat down to play with them. . . we might need another one sooner than expected. :D
